This artifact vendors the "block-dangerous-git.sh" hook script from
mattpocock/skills (the git-guardrails-claude-code skill).

Vendored file (upstream path):
  - skills/misc/git-guardrails-claude-code/scripts/block-dangerous-git.sh

The script is vendored verbatim and was audited before inclusion: it reads the
tool command from stdin (via jq), greps it against a literal list of dangerous
git patterns (push, reset --hard, clean -f/-fd, branch -D, checkout/restore .,
push --force), and exits 2 to block on a match. It performs no network access,
no eval, and no file writes.

Patronus places this script in the agent's hook-script dir and registers the
upstream's PreToolUse Bash hook to invoke it. The surrounding skill prose
(setup instructions) is not vendored — only the script + the hook registration.

